The SwitchPath cat-back system from @awetuningofficial offer two distinct tones in one package. This kit unleashes a signature soundtrack out of the Z06, whether the valves are open or closed, thanks to its specifically tuned straight-through mufflers and precision-engineered x-pipe. It’s aggressive with the valves closed, and viscous with them open–just how a high-revving flat-plane V8 should be. Well-collected and comfortable when cruising (like stock), a riot when ripping, all controlled via the factory controls. If you’re planning on high flow cats, proceed with confidence as we engineered our mufflers to be fully capable of controlling those harsh frequencies. There’s also no need for a post-install visit to your local dealer for a valve relearn. Once it’s on, you’re clear for takeoff. Not only does the SwitchPath feature tier 1 OEM-supplied valves, included in every kit is a set of machined aluminum brackets to accommodate the factory valve motors and their factory linkage, keeping them away from the hot exhaust prolonging the lifespan of the electronics. Further, these valves won’t rattle a year later after installation – others on the market will. Two machined aluminum heat shields bolt-on to the Z06’s bumper using factory mounting points allowing the exhaust to shine through the mesh while protecting the inside of the bumper. No exhaust wraps that will inevitably become waterlogged and cause damage to whatever lies underneath. This exhaust system sheds 15lbs off your car’s weight getting rid of that heavy factory system. Topped off with quad 4.5” double-walled slash-cut tips exclusively in diamond black that fill the Z06’s bumper perfectly without any need for additional filler. The SwitchPath system does not interfere with any factory emissions equipment, so it is 100% emissions friendly, and a lifetime warranty comes standard. 😎

"The purpose of any vehicle audio installation is to provide a premium listening experience with clear, crisp, and emphasized sound. The best way to achieve this is by including sound deadening as part of the installation process.
That way, you ensure the sound you want to hear in your vehicle stays within and that the noise pollution of the road stays out.
Traditional sound deadening options tend to fall short by not approaching sound from various angles. Some are foil based, but lack the density of our butyl rubber. Others use open cell acoustic foam which allows for moisture absorption which can lead to mold and mildew issues. Adhesives that don’t grip as strongly as ours can lead to install slips and gap formations. Our sheets are oversized so installations can be done cleaner with less seams and disruption in the sound waves."

The center channel is primarily responsible for reproducing vocals and center-panned audio content. Adding a dedicated center speaker can significantly improve the clarity and precision of vocals, making it feel like the sound is coming from a specific point in the center of the car.

A center channel also contributes to creating a more realistic and expansive soundstage. It helps anchor the vocals and central sound elements, allowing for a better localization of instruments and vocals, making the listening experience more immersive. With a center channel, you can achieve a more accurate stereo image, ensuring that the sonic elements are precisely placed within the space. This contributes to a more realistic representation of the original recording and enhances the overall listening enjoyment.

Distributing the audio workload among multiple speakers, including a center channel, can help reduce distortion. By allowing each speaker to focus on a specific range of frequencies, you can achieve cleaner and more accurate sound reproduction.

In high-end car audio builds, where attention to detail and audio quality are paramount, a center channel can be an integral part of a sophisticated multi-channel audio setup. This is common in premium audio systems designed to replicate studio-grade sound quality within the confines of a car. 🔊

So, you want an Expedition with the "Stealth" package. You also want captain's chairs in the second row. Well, Ford says no, but Titan says yes!

Ford only sells Expeditions with the stealth package that have a full second row, so our guys took out that little middle seat and fabricated pieces to fill all the mounting points in the floor.

Well, that's awesome but now the seats don't have armrests on the inside. No problem! Our guys disassembled the seats and welded the necessary components into the seat frame to accept factory armrest.

That's great! But the Stealth package features that awesome red stitching that is exclusive to the Stealth package. And they don't sell Stealth package vehicles with armrests on the second row, so those armrests don't exist with red stitching. 

Easy! We pulled all the stitching out of the leather armrest covers and re-stitched them with matching red thread.

So now you have a Stealth Expedition with captain's chairs in the second row and it all looks like it came from the factory that way. Now, THAT'S "stealth". 😎

We also blacked out the window trim, wheels, and color-matched the Ford badges on the front and back. Then, Miguel built this killer sub box to go in the back that beautifully compliments that factory styling.

The moral of the story? If want your ride truly tailored to you, then give us a call. 💪

We know you know the obvious benefits of sound prep and damping. 

But for anybody who may not be an engineer or intimately familiar with physics and the properties of mechanical waves in gases and solids, here's three benefits straight from the SoundShield website!

- Adding SoundShield reduces panel vibration and makes the position of speakers harder to localize creating a more realistic sounding system!
- Adding SoundShield increases the low frequency response performance of midbass to better create the ‘up front bass’ illusion when the speaker is installed in a rigid mounting surface.

Audio is just like nearly everything else in life: success is in the prep!
